{"timestamp":"2026-06-09T08:45:57.962Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"call_g9BswKH913jT8AyBQPamjnZq","output":"Chunk ID: 31b7b8\nWall time: 0.5582 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 8206\nOutput:\n{\"comments\":[{\"author\":\"coderabbitai\",\"body\":\"_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟡 Minor_ | _⚡ Quick win_\\n\\n**Use a stable boundary for participant section slicing.**\\n\\nLines 58-59 use a commented block as the end marker. If that comment is removed, `indexOf` becomes `-1` and the slice covers unintended content, weakening this guard test.\\n\\nAs per coding guidelines, `**/*.spec.ts`: Keep unit tests deterministic and close to source files.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003eSuggested fix\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n```diff\\n-    const participantSection = template.slice(\\n-      template.indexOf('\\u003ch2 class=\\\"title-large\\\"\\u003eParticipants\\u003c/h2\\u003e'),\\n-      template.indexOf('\\u003c!--        \\u003ctable mat-table'),\\n-    );\\n+    const participantsStart = template.indexOf(\\n+      '\\u003ch2 class=\\\"title-large\\\"\\u003eParticipants\\u003c/h2\\u003e',\\n+    );\\n+    const participantsEnd = template.indexOf(\\n+      '\\u003ch2 class=\\\"title-large\\\"\\u003eReceipts\\u003c/h2\\u003e',\\n+      participantsStart,\\n+    );\\n+    expect(participantsStart).toBeGreaterThan(-1);\\n+    expect(participantsEnd).toBeGreaterThan(participantsStart);\\n+    const participantSection = template.slice(participantsStart, participantsEnd);\\n```\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- suggestion_start --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003e📝 Committable suggestion\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003e ‼️ **IMPORTANT**\\n\\u003e Carefully review the code before committing. Ensure that it accurately replaces the highlighted code, contains no missing lines, and has no issues with indentation. Thoroughly test \\u0026 benchmark the code to ensure it meets the requirements.\\n\\n```suggestion\\n    const participantsStart = template.indexOf(\\n      '\\u003ch2 class=\\\"title-large\\\"\\u003eParticipants\\u003c/h2\\u003e',\\n    );\\n    const participantsEnd = template.indexOf(\\n      '\\u003ch2 class=\\\"title-large\\\"\\u003eReceipts\\u003c/h2\\u003e',\\n      participantsStart,\\n    );\\n    expect(participantsStart).toBeGreaterThan(-1);\\n    expect(participantsEnd).toBeGreaterThan(participantsStart);\\n    const participantSection = template.slice(participantsStart, participantsEnd);\\n```\\n\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- suggestion_end --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003e🤖 Prompt for AI Agents\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n```\\nVerify each finding against current code. Fix only still-valid issues, skip the\\nrest with a brief reason, keep changes minimal, and validate.\\n\\nIn `@src/app/events/event-organize/event-organize.spec.ts` around lines 56 - 59,\\nThe slice end boundary is unstable because it uses a commented block marker\\nwhich may be removed; update the test in event-organize.spec.ts to locate\\nparticipantSection more robustly by searching for a stable marker instead (for\\nexample use template.indexOf('\\u003ch2 class=\\\"title-large\\\"\\u003eAgenda\\u003c/h2\\u003e') or the\\nclosing table tag '\\u003c/table\\u003e' that terminates the participants table) and replace\\nthe current template.indexOf('\\u003c!--        \\u003ctable mat-table') with that stable\\nmarker so participantSection = template.slice(template.indexOf('\\u003ch2\\nclass=\\\"title-large\\\"\\u003eParticipants\\u003c/h2\\u003e'), template.indexOf('\\u003ch2\\nclass=\\\"title-large\\\"\\u003eAgenda\\u003c/h2\\u003e')) (or use the closing table search) to make the\\nunit test deterministic.\\n```\\n\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- fingerprinting:phantom:poseidon:hawk --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- cr-comment:v1:f08d985e4e2d3f38bfdb42ab --\\u003e\\n\\n_Source: Coding guidelines_\\n\\n\\u003c!-- This is an auto-generated comment by CodeRabbit --\\u003e\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/evorto-app/app/pull/69#discussion_r3377615922\"}],\"id\":\"PRRT_kwDONgQCms6IBH9D\",\"line\":59,\"path\":\"src/app/events/event-organize/event-organize.spec.ts\"}\n{\"comments\":[{\"author\":\"coderabbitai\",\"body\":\"_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟠 Major_\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003e🧩 Analysis chain\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n🏁 Script executed:\\n\\n```shell\\n#!/bin/bash\\nset -euo pipefail\\nfile=\\\"src/server/discounts/discount-provider-config.ts\\\"\\n\\n# Show file with line numbers around the referenced lines.\\nnl -ba \\\"$file\\\" | sed -n '1,120p'\\n\\n# Extract usages of buyEsnCardUrl and validationMode within the file.\\nrg -n \\\"buyEsnCardUrl|validationMode|maybeBuyUrl|maybeValidationMode|config as\\\" \\\"$file\\\" || true\\n```\\n\\nRepository: evorto-app/app\\n\\nLength of output: 101\\n\\n---\\n\\n🏁 Script executed:\\n\\n```shell\\n#!/bin/bash\\nset -euo pipefail\\nfile=\\\"src/server/discounts/discount-provider-config.ts\\\"\\n\\necho \\\"== File exists? ==\\\"\\nls -la \\\"$file\\\"\\n\\necho\\necho \\\"== Lines 1-160 with numbers (no nl in this sandbox) ==\\\"\\ncat -n \\\"$file\\\" | sed -n '1,160p'\\n\\necho\\necho \\\"== Relevant identifiers in file ==\\\"\\nrg -n \\\"buyEsnCardUrl|validationMode|maybeBuyUrl|maybeValidationMode|config as|Reflect\\\\.get|Object\\\\.hasOwn\\\" \\\"$file\\\" || true\\n```\\n\\nRepository: evorto-app/app\\n\\nLength of output: 3376\\n\\n---\\n\\n\\n\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n**Remove unchecked `as` casts when extracting `buyEsnCardUrl`/`validationMode`**\\n  \\n`normalizeEsnCardConfig` already narrows `config` to an `object`, but it still uses unchecked casts at lines 33–42 to read properties from `unknown`. Replace these reads with `Reflect.get` and keep the existing runtime checks.\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003e♻️ Proposed change\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n```diff\\n-  const maybeBuyUrl = (\\n-    config as {\\n-      buyEsnCardUrl?: unknown;\\n-    }\\n-  ).buyEsnCardUrl;\\n-  const maybeValidationMode = (\\n-    config as {\\n-      validationMode?: unknown;\\n-    }\\n-  ).validationMode;\\n+  const maybeBuyUrl = Reflect.get(config, 'buyEsnCardUrl');\\n+  const maybeValidationMode = Reflect.get(config, 'validationMode');\\n```\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003e🤖 Prompt for AI Agents\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n```\\nVerify each finding against current code. Fix only still-valid issues, skip the\\nrest with a brief reason, keep changes minimal, and validate.\\n\\nIn `@src/server/discounts/discount-provider-config.ts` around lines 38 - 42,\\nnormalizeEsnCardConfig currently uses unchecked \\\"as\\\" casts to extract properties\\n(e.g., buyEsnCardUrl and validationMode) from config into\\nmaybeBuyEsnCardUrl/maybeValidationMode; replace those casts by using\\nReflect.get(config, 'buyEsnCardUrl') and Reflect.get(config, 'validationMode')\\nand keep the existing runtime type checks (e.g., typeof === 'string' or other\\nchecks) so you avoid unsafe type assertions while preserving validation logic;\\nupdate references to maybeBuyEsnCardUrl and maybeValidationMode accordingly.\\n```\\n\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- fingerprinting:phantom:poseidon:hawk --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- cr-comment:v1:8bd4d43818959e6756f4db53 --\\u003e\\n\\n_Source: Coding guidelines_\\n\\n\\u003c!-- This is an auto-generated comment by CodeRabbit --\\u003e\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/evorto-app/app/pull/69#discussion_r3377615949\"}],\"id\":\"PRRT_kwDONgQCms6IBH9S\",\"line\":42,\"path\":\"src/server/discounts/discount-provider-config.ts\"}\n{\"comments\":[{\"author\":\"coderabbitai\",\"body\":\"_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟠 Major_ | _⚡ Quick win_\\n\\n**Enforce integer checks for registration-limit policy values.**\\n\\n`normalizeRegistrationLimitPolicy` currently accepts fractional numbers (for example `1.5`) even though the contract/error states “positive integers”. This can store invalid policy values and break cross-layer assumptions.\\n\\n   \\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003eSuggested fix\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n```diff\\n   if (\\n     registrationLimitCount === null ||\\n     registrationLimitWindowDays === null ||\\n+    !Number.isInteger(registrationLimitCount) ||\\n+    !Number.isInteger(registrationLimitWindowDays) ||\\n     registrationLimitCount \\u003c 1 ||\\n     registrationLimitWindowDays \\u003c 1\\n   ) {\\n```\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003e🤖 Prompt for AI Agents\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n```\\nVerify each finding against current code. Fix only still-valid issues, skip the\\nrest with a brief reason, keep changes minimal, and validate.\\n\\nIn `@src/server/effect/rpc/handlers/admin.handlers.ts` around lines 138 - 146,\\nnormalizeRegistrationLimitPolicy currently only checks for null and positivity\\nbut allows fractional values; update the validation in\\nnormalizeRegistrationLimitPolicy to require integer values for\\nregistrationLimitCount and registrationLimitWindowDays (e.g., use\\nNumber.isInteger or equivalent) and throw the same Error when either value is\\nnon-integer or \\u003c1; ensure any parsing/conversion path that produces\\nregistrationLimitCount/registrationLimitWindowDays enforces integer conversion\\nor rejects fractional inputs so stored policy values are always integers.\\n```\\n\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- fingerprinting:phantom:poseidon:hawk --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- cr-comment:v1:247d06571feea4a56f026d5d --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- This is an auto-generated comment by CodeRabbit --\\u003e\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/evorto-app/app/pull/69#discussion_r3377615953\"}],\"id\":\"PRRT_kwDONgQCms6IBH9W\",\"line\":142,\"path\":\"src/server/effect/rpc/handlers/admin.handlers.ts\"}\n{\"comments\":[{\"author\":\"coderabbitai\",\"body\":\"_🧹 Nitpick_ | _🔵 Trivial_ | _💤 Low value_\\n\\n**Consider passing `pinnedNowIso` for e2e test consistency.**\\n\\nThe main `registerForEvent` flow resolves `pinnedNowIso` from server config and passes it to `buildCheckoutSessionExpiresAt`. This handler doesn't, which could cause checkout session expiry inconsistencies in e2e tests with pinned time.\\n\\nIf e2e tests don't exercise this path with pinned time, this is low priority.\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003e🤖 Prompt for AI Agents\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n```\\nVerify each finding against current code. Fix only still-valid issues, skip the\\nrest with a brief reason, keep changes minimal, and validate.\\n\\nIn `@src/server/effect/rpc/handlers/events/events-registration.handlers.ts` around\\nlines 1981 - 1985, This handler calls buildCheckoutSessionExpiresAt without the\\ntest time override, causing e2e flakiness; update the events-registration\\nhandler (the createHostedCheckoutSession call in\\nevents-registration.handlers.ts) to resolve the same pinnedNowIso from server\\nconfig (the same value used in registerForEvent) and pass pinnedNowIso into\\nbuildCheckoutSessionExpiresAt so the checkout session expiry is computed\\nconsistently for pinned-time tests.\\n```\\n\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- fingerprinting:phantom:medusa:ocelot --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- cr-comment:v1:c01f0e93f0bbcf453db4d0ef --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- This is an auto-generated comment by CodeRabbit --\\u003e\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/evorto-app/app/pull/69#discussion_r3377615958\"}],\"id\":\"PRRT_kwDONgQCms6IBH9a\",\"line\":2009,\"path\":\"src/server/effect/rpc/handlers/events/events-registration.handlers.ts\"}\n{\"comments\":[{\"author\":\"coderabbitai\",\"body\":\"_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟠 Major_ | _⚡ Quick win_\\n\\n**Re-check receipt status atomically in the update WHERE clause.**\\n\\nLine 705 currently updates by `tenantId + id` only. A concurrent status change (e.g., to `refunded`) between the initial read and this update can pass and produce conflicting receipt state.\\n\\n  \\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003eSuggested fix\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n```diff\\n             const updatedReceipts = yield* tx\\n               .update(financeReceipts)\\n               .set({\\n@@\\n               .where(\\n                 and(\\n                   eq(financeReceipts.tenantId, tenant.id),\\n                   eq(financeReceipts.id, input.id),\\n+                  eq(financeReceipts.status, receipt.status),\\n                 ),\\n               )\\n@@\\n             const updatedReceipt = updatedReceipts[0];\\n             if (!updatedReceipt) {\\n-              return null;\\n+              return yield* Effect.fail(\\n+                new RpcBadRequestError({\\n+                  message: 'Receipt review preconditions failed',\\n+                  reason: 'receiptReviewPreconditionFailed',\\n+                }),\\n+              );\\n             }\\n```\\n\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n\\nAlso applies to: 717-719, 784-792\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003e🤖 Prompt for AI Agents\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n```\\nVerify each finding against current code. Fix only still-valid issues, skip the\\nrest with a brief reason, keep changes minimal, and validate.\\n\\nIn `@src/server/effect/rpc/handlers/finance/finance-receipts.handlers.ts` around\\nlines 705 - 709, The update WHERE clauses that currently match only on tenantId\\nand id (using financeReceipts, tenant.id and input.id) must also atomically\\ncheck the current receipt status to prevent races; modify the AND conditions in\\nthe update queries (the clauses around financeReceipts.id and\\nfinanceReceipts.tenantId) to include an equality check for the expected status\\n(e.g., financeReceipts.status === expectedStatus or input.expectedStatus) so the\\nUPDATE only succeeds if the status hasn’t changed concurrently — apply the same\\nchange to the other similar update sites referenced (the blocks around the calls\\nat the locations noted: the clauses at ~717-719 and ~784-792) and ensure the\\ncode handles a zero-rows-updated result as a concurrent-modification error path.\\n```\\n\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- fingerprinting:phantom:poseidon:hawk --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- cr-comment:v1:ad3f82d54e0b676a86314a6d --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- This is an auto-generated comment by CodeRabbit --\\u003e\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/evorto-app/app/pull/69#discussion_r3377615961\"}],\"id\":\"PRRT_kwDONgQCms6IBH9c\",\"line\":709,\"path\":\"src/server/effect/rpc/handlers/finance/finance-receipts.handlers.ts\"}\n{\"comments\":[{\"author\":\"coderabbitai\",\"body\":\"_🧹 Nitpick_ | _🔵 Trivial_ | _💤 Low value_\\n\\n**Consider replacing shift-based mock with explicit call tracking.**\\n\\nThe `selectRows.shift()` pattern on line 234 makes test behavior depend on the exact order and count of select queries. If the handler implementation changes query order or adds queries, the test will silently return incorrect mock data or fail unexpectedly.\\n\\nConsider tracking calls explicitly and returning appropriate data based on query criteria rather than call order.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003e♻️ Alternative approach\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n```diff\\n-  const selectRows = [\\n-    [\\n-      {\\n-        communicationEmail: 'notify@example.com',\\n-        email: 'login@example.com',\\n-        firstName: 'Alice',\\n-      },\\n-    ],\\n-    [\\n-      {\\n-        title: 'City Walk',\\n-      },\\n-    ],\\n-  ];\\n   const selectQuery = {\\n     from: () =\\u003e selectQuery,\\n-    limit: () =\\u003e Effect.succeed(selectRows.shift() ?? []),\\n+    limit: (count: number) =\\u003e {\\n+      // Return data based on query context instead of call order\\n+      // Implementation depends on how to distinguish user vs event query\\n+      return Effect.succeed([/* appropriate data */]);\\n+    },\\n     where: () =\\u003e selectQuery,\\n   };\\n```\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003e🤖 Prompt for AI Agents\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n```\\nVerify each finding against current code. Fix only still-valid issues, skip the\\nrest with a brief reason, keep changes minimal, and validate.\\n\\nIn `@src/server/effect/rpc/handlers/finance/finance.handlers.spec.ts` around lines\\n218 - 236, The test uses a shifting array (selectRows.shift()) inside\\nselectQuery.limit(), which couples returned mock rows to call order; change the\\nmock to track calls explicitly and return data based on call context: replace\\nselectRows/selectQuery.shift usage with a call counter or inspect the query\\ncriteria passed to methods on selectQuery, then have selectQuery.limit() return\\nEffect.succeed(...) with the correct row set for that specific call (e.g., using\\na counter variable like selectCallCount or branching on parameters) so the mock\\nreturns the intended user vs. title rows regardless of query ordering; update\\nreferences to selectRows, selectQuery, and the Effect.succeed(...) return to use\\nthis explicit logic.\\n```\\n\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- fingerprinting:phantom:poseidon:puma --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- cr-comment:v1:fc7e8934ec2eb7bcbeb554e9 --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- This is an auto-generated comment by CodeRabbit --\\u003e\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/evorto-app/app/pull/69#discussion_r3377615965\"}],\"id\":\"PRRT_kwDONgQCms6IBH9f\",\"line\":236,\"path\":\"src/server/effect/rpc/handlers/finance/finance.handlers.spec.ts\"}\n{\"comments\":[{\"author\":\"coderabbitai\",\"body\":\"_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟠 Major_ | _⚡ Quick win_\\n\\n**Add a timeout/cancellation path for outbound Resend requests.**\\n\\nA hung `emailFetch` call can block `runOnce` indefinitely and stall the dispatcher loop. Bound this call with timeout + abort so the item can be marked failed and retried safely.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003eSuggested patch\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n```diff\\n const sendWithResend = ({\\n   emailFetch = fetch,\\n   notification,\\n   settings,\\n }: {\\n   emailFetch?: EmailFetch | undefined;\\n   notification: EmailNotificationRow;\\n   settings: ResendEmailSettings;\\n }) =\\u003e\\n   Effect.tryPromise({\\n     catch: dispatchFailureMessage,\\n     try: async () =\\u003e {\\n+      const controller = new AbortController();\\n+      const timeout = setTimeout(() =\\u003e controller.abort(), 15_000);\\n+\\n+      try {\\n       const response = await emailFetch(resendEmailsEndpoint, {\\n         body: JSON.stringify({\\n           from: settings.fromAddress,\\n           subject: notification.subject,\\n           text: notification.textBody,\\n           to: [notification.recipientEmail],\\n         }),\\n         headers: {\\n           Authorization: `Bearer ${settings.apiKey}`,\\n           'Content-Type': 'application/json',\\n           'User-Agent': 'evorto-email-outbox/1.0',\\n         },\\n         method: 'POST',\\n+        signal: controller.signal,\\n       });\\n \\n       if (!response.ok) {\\n         const responseText = await response.text();\\n         throw new Error(\\n           `Resend email send failed with status ${response.status}: ${responseText}`,\\n         );\\n       }\\n+      } finally {\\n+        clearTimeout(timeout);\\n+      }\\n     },\\n   });\\n```\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- suggestion_start --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003e📝 Committable suggestion\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003e ‼️ **IMPORTANT**\\n\\u003e Carefully review the code before committing. Ensure that it accurately replaces the highlighted code, contains no missing lines, and has no issues with indentation. Thoroughly test \\u0026 benchmark the code to ensure it meets the requirements.\\n\\n```suggestion\\nconst sendWithResend = ({\\n  emailFetch = fetch,\\n  notification,\\n  settings,\\n}: {\\n  emailFetch?: EmailFetch | undefined;\\n  notification: EmailNotificationRow;\\n  settings: ResendEmailSettings;\\n}) =\\u003e\\n  Effect.tryPromise({\\n    catch: dispatchFailureMessage,\\n    try: async () =\\u003e {\\n      const controller = new AbortController();\\n      const timeout = setTimeout(() =\\u003e controller.abort(), 15_000);\\n\\n      try {\\n        const response = await emailFetch(resendEmailsEndpoint, {\\n          body: JSON.stringify({\\n            from: settings.fromAddress,\\n            subject: notification.subject,\\n            text: notification.textBody,\\n            to: [notification.recipientEmail],\\n          }),\\n          headers: {\\n            Authorization: `Bearer ${settings.apiKey}`,\\n            'Content-Type': 'application/json',\\n            'User-Agent': 'evorto-email-outbox/1.0',\\n          },\\n          method: 'POST',\\n          signal: controller.signal,\\n        });\\n\\n        if (!response.ok) {\\n          const responseText = await response.text();\\n          throw new Error(\\n            `Resend email send failed with status ${response.status}: ${responseText}`,\\n          );\\n        }\\n      } finally {\\n        clearTimeout(timeout);\\n      }\\n    },\\n  });\\n```\\n\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- suggestion_end --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003e🤖 Prompt for AI Agents\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n```\\nVerify each finding against current code. Fix only still-valid issues, skip the\\nrest with a brief reason, keep changes minimal, and validate.\\n\\nIn `@src/server/email/email-notification-dispatcher.ts` around lines 68 - 103, The\\noutbound Resend call in sendWithResend can hang indefinitely; wrap the\\nemailFetch call with an AbortController and a timeout so requests are aborted\\nafter a bounded period and the dispatcher (runOnce) can mark and retry failures.\\nConcretely, create an AbortController, pass its signal into the emailFetch\\noptions (alongside existing headers/body/method), start a timer (e.g.,\\nconfigurable timeout) that calls controller.abort() when elapsed, and clear the\\ntimer on success or error; when aborting, throw a distinguishable error so\\ndispatchFailureMessage can handle it the same as other send failures. Ensure the\\ntimer is always cleared and the signal is used with\\nemailFetch/resendEmailsEndpoint in sendWithResend.\\n```\\n\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- fingerprinting:phantom:poseidon:hawk --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- cr-comment:v1:2ed297f353bee2c683584965 --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- This is an auto-generated comment by CodeRabbit --\\u003e\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/evorto-app/app/pull/69#discussion_r3377615970\"}],\"id\":\"PRRT_kwDONgQCms6IBH9j\",\"line\":103,\"path\":\"src/server/email/email-notification-dispatcher.ts\"}\n{\"comments\":[{\"author\":\"coderabbitai\",\"body\":\"_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟠 Major_ | _🏗️ Heavy lift_\\n\\n**Add atomic claim semantics before sending outbox rows.**\\n\\n`loadDispatchableNotifications` reads `pending/failed` rows without claiming them first. Multiple app instances can pick the same rows and send duplicate emails; repeatedly failed old rows can also starve newer pending rows. Move to a transactional “claim then send” flow (e.g., `processing` state + lease/attempt metadata, `SKIP LOCKED`/equivalent).\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003e🤖 Prompt for AI Agents\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n```\\nVerify each finding against current code. Fix only still-valid issues, skip the\\nrest with a brief reason, keep changes minimal, and validate.\\n\\nIn `@src/server/email/email-notification-dispatcher.ts` around lines 107 - 139,\\nloadDispatchableNotifications currently selects pending/failed rows without\\nclaiming them, causing duplicate sends; change it to a transactional \\\"claim then\\nreturn\\\" flow: in a transaction, atomically UPDATE emailNotificationOutbox rows\\nmatching status IN ('pending','failed') ordered by createdAt LIMIT batchSize to\\nset status='processing', set a lease/attempt metadata (e.g.,\\nprocessingExpiresAt, attemptCount++), using SKIP LOCKED or SELECT ... FOR UPDATE\\nSKIP LOCKED as supported, then SELECT and return those claimed rows; update\\nmarkNotificationFailed and markNotificationSent to clear processing fields\\n(processingExpiresAt, status -\\u003e 'failed' or 'sent') and to increment/record\\nattempt metadata consistently so retries and lease expirations behave correctly.\\n```\\n\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- fingerprinting:phantom:poseidon:hawk --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- cr-comment:v1:f5e22192f7a10fd77219e982 --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- This is an auto-generated comment by CodeRabbit --\\u003e\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/evorto-app/app/pull/69#discussion_r3377615977\"}],\"id\":\"PRRT_kwDONgQCms6IBH9p\",\"line\":139,\"path\":\"src/server/email/email-notification-dispatcher.ts\"}\n{\"comments\":[{\"author\":\"coderabbitai\",\"body\":\"_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟠 Major_\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003e🧩 Analysis chain\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n🏁 Script executed:\\n\\n```shell\\n#!/bin/bash\\nset -euo pipefail\\n\\nFILE=\\\"src/server/http/stripe-webhook.web-handler.ts\\\"\\n\\necho \\\"== Context around Promise.race (lines ~150-220) ==\\\"\\nsed -n '130,230p' \\\"$FILE\\\" | nl -ba | sed 's/^/| /'\\n\\necho\\necho \\\"== Locate insertPendingTransferRefundRecord usage ==\\\"\\nrg -n \\\"insertPendingTransferRefundRecord\\\" \\\"$FILE\\\" || true\\n\\necho\\necho \\\"== Find definition(s) of insertPendingTransferRefundRecord ==\\\"\\nfd -a \\\"insertPendingTransferRefundRecord\\\" . -t f || true\\nrg -n \\\"function insertPendingTransferRefundRecord|const insertPendingTransferRefundRecord|insertPendingTransferRefundRecord\\\\s*[:=]\\\\s*\\\\(\\\" . -S --glob='*.ts' --glob='*.tsx' || true\\n\\necho\\necho \\\"== Inspect definition file(s) if found ==\\\"\\nDEF_FILES=$(rg -l \\\"insertPendingTransferRefundRecord\\\" . -S --glob='*.ts' --glob='*.tsx' || true)\\nif [ -n \\\"${DEF_FILES}\\\" ]; then\\n  echo \\\"$DEF_FILES\\\" | head -n 20\\nfi\\n\\necho\\npython3 - \\u003c\\u003c'PY'\\nimport subprocess, os, textwrap, sys, re, json, pathlib\\ndef run(cmd):\\n    return subprocess.run(cmd, shell=True, check=False, stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.STDOUT, text=True).stdout\\n# pick up to 5 files containing the symbol and print small excerpts around the first occurrence\\ncmd = \\\"rg -l \\\\\\\"insertPendingTransferRefundRecord\\\\\\\" . -S --glob='*.ts' --glob='*.tsx'\\\"\\nout = run(cmd).strip().splitlines()\\nprint(\\\"Found files:\\\", len(out))\\nfor f in out[:5]:\\n    print(\\\"\\\\n---\\\", f, \\\"---\\\")\\n    # show 80 lines around first match\\n    show = run(f\\\"rg -n \\\\\\\"insertPendingTransferRefundRecord\\\\\\\" {subprocess.quote(f)} -m 1\\\")\\n    print(show.strip())\\n    # extract line number\\n    m = re.search(r\\\":(\\\\d+):\\\", show)\\n    if not m: \\n        continue\\n    line = int(m.group(1))\\n    start = max(1, line-40)\\n    end = line+60\\n    content = run(f\\\"sed -n '{start},{end}p' {subprocess.quote(f)} | nl -ba | sed 's/^/| /'\\\")\\n    print(content)\\nPY\\n\\necho\\necho \\\"== Search for any dedupe/idempotency related to pending transfer refund records ==\\\"\\nrg -n \\\"pending.*transfer.*refund|transfer.*refund.*pending|refundTransaction|dedup|idempot\\\" src/server src/db src/shared . -S --glob='*.ts' --glob='*.tsx' | head -n 200\\n\\necho\\necho \\\"== Search for 'Stripe refund creation timed out' references ==\\\"\\nrg -n \\\"Stripe refund creation timed out\\\" . -S --glob='*.ts' --glob='*.tsx' || true\\n```\\n\\nRepository: evorto-app/app\\n\\nLength of output: 170\\n\\n---\\n\\n🏁 Script executed:\\n\\n```shell\\n#!/bin/bash\\nset -euo pipefail\\n\\nFILE=\\\"src/server/http/stripe-webhook.web-handler.ts\\\"\\n\\necho \\\"== Context around Promise.race (lines 130-230) ==\\\"\\nsed -n '130,230p' \\\"$FILE\\\" | awk '{printf \\\"%6d|%s\\\\n\\\", NR+129, $0}'\\n\\necho\\necho \\\"== Locate insertPendingTransferRefundRecord usage in stripe-webhook handler ==\\\"\\nrg -n \\\"insertPendingTransferRefundRecord\\\" \\\"$FILE\\\" || true\\n\\necho\\necho \\\"== Find definition(s) of insertPendingTransferRefundRecord ==\\\"\\nDEF_FILES=$(rg -l \\\"insertPendingTransferRefundRecord\\\" . -S --glob='*.ts' --glob='*.tsx' || true)\\necho \\\"$DEF_FILES\\\" | head -n 20\\n\\necho\\necho \\\"== Inspect first match vicinity for up to 3 definition files ==\\\"\\ni=0\\nwhile IFS= read -r f; do\\n  [ -z \\\"$f\\\" ] \\u0026\\u0026 continue\\n  i=$((i+1))\\n  line=$(rg -n -m1 \\\"insertPendingTransferRefundRecord\\\" \\\"$f\\\" -S --glob='*.ts' --glob='*.tsx' | cut -d: -f1)\\n  start=$((line-40)); [ $start -lt 1 ] \\u0026\\u0026 start=1\\n  end=$((line+70))\\n  echo\\n  echo \\\"--- $f (first match line $line) ---\\\"\\n  sed -n \\\"${start},${end}p\\\" \\\"$f\\\" | awk -v off=\\\"$start\\\" '{printf \\\"%6d|%s\\\\n\\\", off+NR-1, $0}'\\n  [ $i -ge 3 ] \\u0026\\u0026 break\\ndone \\u003c\\u003c\\u003c \\\"$DEF_FILES\\\"\\n\\necho\\necho \\\"== Search for dedupe/idempotency related to pending transfer refund records ==\\\"\\nrg -n \\\"pending.*transfer.*refund|transfer.*refund.*pending|refundTransaction|dedup|idempot|unique\\\" src -S --glob='*.ts' --glob='*.tsx' | head -n 200 || true\\n\\necho\\necho \\\"== Search for pending/manual transfer refund insertion and reconciliation/update paths ==\\\"\\nrg -n \\\"pending.*refund|manual.*refund|transfer.*refund\\\" src/server src/db src/shared -S --glob='*.ts' --glob='*.tsx' | head -n 200 || true\\n\\necho\\necho \\\"== Search in stripe-webhook handler for refund event handling/update logic ==\\\"\\nrg -n \\\"refund\\\" \\\"$FILE\\\" -S --glob='*.ts' --glob='*.tsx' | head -n 200 || true\\n\\necho\\necho \\\"== Search for 'Stripe refund creation timed out' references ==\\\"\\nrg -n \\\"Stripe refund creation timed out\\\" . -S --glob='*.ts' --glob='*.tsx' || true\\n```\\n\\nRepository: evorto-app/app\\n\\nLength of output: 31621\\n\\n---\\n\\n\\n\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n**Fix Stripe refund timeout handling to avoid creating false “manual pending” records.**  \\n\\nIn `src/server/http/stripe-webhook.web-handler.ts`, the `Promise.race` at lines 157-166 rejects on the 5s timer without canceling the underlying `stripe.refunds.create` request; when that timeout wins, the `Effect.catch` at lines 187-203 inserts a pending `insertPendingTransferRefundRecord(...)` (`manuallyCreated: true`). If the Stripe refund succeeds after the timeout, this can leave an incorrect pending/manual follow-up (and potential duplicate handling) with no reconciliation/cleanup from the eventual Stripe outcome.\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003e🤖 Prompt for AI Agents\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n```\\nVerify each finding against current code. Fix only still-valid issues, skip the\\nrest with a brief reason, keep changes minimal, and validate.\\n\\nIn `@src/server/http/stripe-webhook.web-handler.ts` around lines 157 - 167, The\\nPromise.race timeout can leave the underlying stripe.refunds.create running and\\nlater succeed, causing incorrect\\ninsertPendingTransferRefundRecord(manuallyCreated: true); fix by wiring an\\nAbortController into the stripe.refunds.create call and aborting the request\\nwhen the timeout fires, and also clear the timeout when stripe.refunds.create\\nresolves so no stray timers remain. Concretely, create an AbortController, pass\\nits signal into stripe.refunds.create(stripeRefundParameters, { stripeAccount,\\nsignal }), replace the raw Promise.race with a timeout that calls\\ncontroller.abort() and rejects with a distinct timeout Error, and ensure the\\nsuccess path clears the timer; keep the Effect.tryPromise and the downstream\\nEffect.catch but use the distinct timeout error to avoid inserting a manual\\npending record for aborted/timeouts.\\n```\\n\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- fingerprinting:phantom:poseidon:hawk --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- cr-comment:v1:7a78c7dcaff3c21075d9290d --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- This is an auto-generated comment by CodeRabbit --\\u003e\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/evorto-app/app/pull/69#discussion_r3377615981\"}],\"id\":\"PRRT_kwDONgQCms6IBH9t\",\"line\":167,\"path\":\"src/server/http/stripe-webhook.web-handler.ts\"}\n{\"comments\":[{\"author\":\"coderabbitai\",\"body\":\"_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟠 Major_ | _⚡ Quick win_\\n\\n**Constrain registration-limit fields to valid domain values at the RPC boundary.**\\n\\n`Schema.Int` still accepts negative values here, so invalid tenant policy can be persisted through a valid decode. These fields should be derived from constrained tenant field schemas (or explicitly bounded) instead of raw ints.\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003e💡 Suggested fix\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n```diff\\n export const AdminTenantUpdateSettingsInput = Schema.Struct({\\n@@\\n-  registrationLimitCount: Schema.optional(Schema.Int),\\n-  registrationLimitWindowDays: Schema.optional(Schema.Int),\\n+  registrationLimitCount: Schema.optional(Tenant.fields.registrationLimitCount),\\n+  registrationLimitWindowDays: Schema.optional(\\n+    Tenant.fields.registrationLimitWindowDays,\\n+  ),\\n@@\\n });\\n```\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\nAs per coding guidelines, “Server boundaries must use Effect Schema for validated input/output.”\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003e🤖 Prompt for AI Agents\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n```\\nVerify each finding against current code. Fix only still-valid issues, skip the\\nrest with a brief reason, keep changes minimal, and validate.\\n\\nIn `@src/shared/rpc-contracts/app-rpcs/admin.rpcs.ts` around lines 222 - 223, The\\nRPC schema uses raw Schema.Int for registrationLimitCount and\\nregistrationLimitWindowDays which allows negatives; replace those with validated\\nEffect Schemas (or reuse the tenant-model's constrained registration-limit\\nschemas) so the RPC boundary enforces domain constraints (e.g., non-negative\\nintegers and any applicable upper bound) and keep them optional\\n(Schema.optional) so invalid negative values are rejected during decode.\\n```\\n\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- fingerprinting:phantom:poseidon:hawk --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- cr-comment:v1:983befa8340573908f225c39 --\\u003e\\n\\n_Source: Coding guidelines_\\n\\n\\u003c!-- This is an auto-generated comment by CodeRabbit --\\u003e\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/evorto-app/app/pull/69#discussion_r3377615988\"}],\"id\":\"PRRT_kwDONgQCms6IBH9w\",\"line\":223,\"path\":\"src/shared/rpc-contracts/app-rpcs/admin.rpcs.ts\"}\n"}}
