              continue;\\n-            }\\n-\\n-            const source = readFileSync(file, 'utf8');\\n-            if (\\n-              source.includes(privateRegistry) ||\\n-              privatePackage.test(source) ||\\n-              (privateDuotonePackage.test(source) \\u0026\\u0026 !source.includes(publicDuotoneAlias))\\n-            ) {\\n-              console.error(`::error file=${file}::Font Awesome must stay on free public npm packages in CI.`);\\n-              failed = true;\\n-            }\\n-          }\\n-\\n-          if (failed) {\\n-            process.exit(1);\\n-          }\\n-          NODE\\n+      - name: Enforce public Font Awesome dependencies\\n+        run: bash helpers/testing/prepare-public-fontawesome-ci.sh\\n```\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003cdetails\\u003e\\n\\u003csummary\\u003e🤖 Prompt for AI Agents\\u003c/summary\\u003e\\n\\n```\\nVerify each finding against current code. Fix only still-valid issues, skip the\\nrest with a brief reason, keep changes minimal, and validate.\\n\\nIn @.github/workflows/copilot-setup-steps.yml around lines 52 - 95, Replace the\\nduplicated Font Awesome preflight logic in the two workflow steps (\\\"Force public\\nFont Awesome registry\\\" and \\\"Validate public Font Awesome dependencies\\\") with a\\nsingle invocation of the existing helper script\\nhelpers/testing/prepare-public-fontawesome-ci.sh; specifically, drop the inline\\nshell block and node script and instead run or source that helper so it sets\\nNPM_CONFIG_USERCONFIG, clears NPM_CONFIG_GLOBALCONFIG, and scrubs Font Awesome\\ntoken env vars as the canonical policy requires; ensure the workflow step runs\\nthe helper with executable permissions (or sources it) so its environment\\nexports (NPM_CONFIG_USERCONFIG) and failure exit codes are preserved.\\n```\\n\\n\\u003c/details\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- fingerprinting:phantom:medusa:grasshopper --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- cr-comment:v1:0aedd9625a0b04c0b3b9367e --\\u003e\\n\\n\\u003c!-- Th