{"timestamp":"2026-06-09T09:00:21.139Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"thread_goal_updated","threadId":"019ea60b-1a1c-7703-b8d8-26ed57eb7f8e","turnId":"e0ac55d5-8f6b-48f1-ba5b-f3c66ecc8c8e","goal":{"threadId":"019ea60b-1a1c-7703-b8d8-26ed57eb7f8e","objective":"Finalize the stacked split PRs for evorto-app/app#62 from lowest to highest PR number. For each PR #63 through #71, inspect unresolved review comments and failing checks, verify whether downstream stacked PRs already address each issue, make only the minimal necessary fixes, reply to comments when no code change is needed, resolve completed threads, and keep every split PR ready for review with no PR over 150 changed files. \nOnce one PR is done, you can set the next one to ready for review so coderabbit will check. Try to avoid rate limits. Preserve the final stacked code state so the top split branch remains equivalent to the current PR #62 assembly branch.","status":"active","tokensUsed":14799347,"timeUsedSeconds":75321,"createdAt":1780920299,"updatedAt":1780995621}}}
{"timestamp":"2026-06-09T09:00:21.143Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"call_efDC7HfWEqDgjUDwce7mQd8R","output":"Chunk ID: c95103\nWall time: 0.4730 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 594\nOutput:\n{\"changedFiles\":118,\"isDraft\":false,\"number\":71,\"unresolved\":{\"count\":3,\"threads\":[{\"id\":\"PRRT_kwDONgQCms6H-lwg\",\"isOutdated\":false,\"line\":82,\"path\":\"package.json\",\"title\":\"**\\u003csub\\u003e\\u003csub\\u003e![P1 Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/P1-orange?style=flat)\\u003c/sub\\u003e\\u003c/sub\\u003e  Restore the Font Awesome import path before dropping the alias** When installing from this package.json, `@fortawesome/duotone-regular-svg-icons` is no longer present, but the app still imports that module in many source files (for example `src/shared/permissions/permissions.ts` and numerous Angular components). A fresh install from this lockfile will therefore leave those imports unresolved and the app/tests cannot build until the imports are migrated or the alias dependency is restored.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/evorto-app/app/pull/71#discussion_r3376686681\"},{\"id\":\"PRRT_kwDONgQCms6H-lwi\",\"isOutdated\":false,\"line\":243,\"path\":\".github/workflows/e2e-baseline.yml\",\"title\":\"**\\u003csub\\u003e\\u003csub\\u003e![P1 Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/P1-orange?style=flat)\\u003c/sub\\u003e\\u003c/sub\\u003e  Make E2E wait for the cache warmer before offline install** In this workflow the `e2e` job has no `needs: warm-ci-caches`, so GitHub can schedule it in parallel with the warmer. On a cold cache or after a lockfile change, this `offline-required` install path will see no dependency-tree cache yet and `helpers/testing/install-ci-dependencies.sh` exits at its missing-cache branch, failing the E2E job instead of letting the warmer populate the cache first.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/evorto-app/app/pull/71#discussion_r3376686684\"},{\"id\":\"PRRT_kwDONgQCms6IBljY\",\"isOutdated\":false,\"line\":25,\"path\":\"package.json\",\"title\":\"**\\u003csub\\u003e\\u003csub\\u003e![P2 Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/P2-yellow?style=flat)\\u003c/sub\\u003e\\u003c/sub\\u003e  Add the missing MCP planner seed** This new script points Playwright at `tests/setup/mcp-browser.seed.ts`, but that file is not present in the committed tree (repo-wide search only finds `tests/setup/mcp-browser-authenticated.seed.ts`). As a result, running `bun run test:e2e:mcp-browser-planner` or the new `mcp-browser-planner` project fails with no matching test file instead of providing the documented public Browser planning seed.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/evorto-app/app/pull/71#discussion_r3377797444\"}]}}\n"}}
